Build bookworm-gnome sdcard for Radxa rockpi4b:

Input files: ../rootfs-bookworm/linaro-esp.img
             ../rootfs-bookworm/linaro-rootfs.img

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
Eject NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD from PC.

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD to rockpi4b.
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Setup wifi. Disable power saving and screen saver.
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sync
sudo shutdown -h now
Power off, power on
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check if Debian is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Check audio driver: ( pulseaudio or pipewire )
pactl info

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools chromium chromium-sandbox ffmpeg mpv glmark2-es2-x11 glmark2-es2-wayland pandoc

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2-wayland   ( for wayland )
glmark2-es2           ( for x11 )

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select card 1 as default )

Chromium -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' hyUhEjtlDLA -o avemaria.mp4
mpv avemaria.mp4

sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
